name: Ilona Maher
summary: American rugby athlete Ilona Maher is rapidly gaining recognition for both her athletic achievements and her social media presence. Known for her TikTok videos, Maher has used her platform to promote rugby while showcasing her journey as a member of the 2024 U.S. Olympic rugby sevens team. Maher's captivating social media posts during the 2024 Paris Games have garnered widespread attention, highlighting her playful side and her ability to connect with audiences. Despite facing criticism about her weight, Maher has responded with resilience and self-assurance. Her team's impressive performance, remaining undefeated alongside New Zealand, Australia, and France, further solidifies Maher's status as a rising star in the world of rugby.

name: Dollywood flooding
summary: Torrential rainfall resulted in severe flash flooding at Dollywood theme park in Sevier County, Tennessee. The heavy downpours led to widespread flooding, leaving at least one person injured. Guests were forced to wade through knee-deep water as portions of the park, including the Splash Country waterpark, were inundated. The flooding occurred after days of heavy rainfall and thunderstorms, causing an "unprecedented flooding event." Park officials evacuated guests and closed attractions due to the safety concerns. Authorities are investigating the extent of the damage and assessing the situation.

name: United Airlines flight diverted
summary: A United Airlines flight from Houston to Boston was diverted to Washington Dulles International Airport on Sunday after a "biohazard" incident. The incident, according to passengers, was caused by an ill passenger who made several flight attendants vomit. As a result, the plane was diverted and underwent a "deep clean" before continuing its journey to Boston. The exact nature of the "biohazard" is unclear, but passengers reported symptoms including nausea and vomiting, leading to speculation that it may have been a contagious illness or food poisoning. The incident highlights the potential health risks associated with air travel, particularly during a pandemic, and the importance of following health guidelines and reporting any health concerns to flight attendants.

In other developments, North Korea has used military helicopters to assist flood victims. The country may also conduct a nuclear missile test around the US election, according to South Korea. Additionally, North Korea has employed fake IT workers from North Korea, and Belarus' foreign minister has arrived in North Korea likely to discuss cooperation with Russia.

CNN highlights US concerns over the election, while Al Jazeera focuses on the challenges Maduro's grip on power faced. WLS-TV covers the reactions of Venezuelans in Chicago. Additionally, The Associated Press reports on Venezuelans' resort to odd jobs and gambling to cope with meager wages and hopes for economic improvement post-election.

name: Suni Lee
summary: Suni Lee, the Olympic gold medalist gymnast, is set to make a comeback at the Paris 2024 Games despite facing health challenges. In 2023, Lee was diagnosed with a rare kidney disease that required hospitalization. However, she has since recovered and is preparing for the upcoming Olympics. Lee's story is one of triumph over adversity, highlighting her resilience and determination to return to the top of the gymnastics world. Her upcoming performance at the Paris Games is highly anticipated, and she is expected to compete alongside fellow Olympic champion Simone Biles.

name: Leon Marchand
summary: French swimmer Léon Marchand has become a national hero after his stunning victory in the 400-meter individual medley at the 2024 Paris Olympics. The 20-year-old set an Olympic record and thrilled the home crowd with his dominant performance, leaving behind the world's best swimmers. Marchand, who trains in the United States, captured the gold medal in a time of 4:02.95, bringing immense pride and joy to France. His triumph marks the country's first swimming gold in the Olympics, making him an instant sensation and sparking widespread admiration.

Morel, known for his vibrant personality and impressive offensive skills, received an emotional farewell from the team during a mid-game announcement of the trade. The Cubs' acquisition of Paredes, a skilled defender with some offensive upside, aligns with their long-term rebuilding plan.

summary: Team USA's head coach, Steve Kerr, has clarified the reasons for benching Jayson Tatum in the opening game of the 2024 Paris Olympics against Serbia. Tatum himself has expressed understanding and support for the decision, acknowledging the importance of team chemistry and cohesion.

name: Fantastic Four
summary: Marvel has unveiled the official title for its upcoming "Fantastic Four" movie as "The Fantastic 4: First Steps." The news was revealed at Comic-Con, where cast members, including Pedro Pascal, made an appearance. The concept footage shared at the event featured a retro 1960s aesthetic, showcasing a vision of Galactus' head. The movie is not an origin story, and the core four characters will appear in the next two "Avengers" movies. Marvel also announced that "The Fantastic 4: First Steps" will be set in the 1960s. The title and footage have generated excitement at Comic-Con, marking a new chapter for the iconic superhero team within the Marvel Cinematic Universe.
